   CHILE-THERAPY (Santiago, Chile) _ Since the arrest last year of
Gen. Augusto Pinochet, psychologists report that hundreds, if not
thousands, of people tortured under his dictatorship have finally
begun to see therapists, to organize group therapy and to share
their long-hidden horrors with spouses and children. By Clifford
