   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 
The Arizona Republic plans to move the following stories for use by
clients of the NYTimes News Service for Monday, Jan. 3. If you have
any questions, please call the Republic News Desk at (602)
444-8286.
<TEXT>
<P>
   &QL; 
MENTAL (Phoenix) _ Fewer and fewer people in the Phoenix area
entering the state's mental health system under the category of
``seriously mentally ill.'' A crackdown in eligibility by state
officials is swamping mental health advocates _ paid by the state
to police the system _ and forcing advocates to turn people away, a
possible violation of state law. Under an increasingly rigid
process, even people ordered by Superior Court judges to be
