ill, or SMI. By JODIE SNYDER. Story will move in the ``A''
category.
</P>
<P>
   VOTING (Phoenix) _ This year, Arizonans will be able to vote for
president about as often as they get an oil change _ and it will
all be legal. Under the current presidential primary arrangement,
voters could legally cast ballots in the primary elections of the
two major political parties, election and party officials concede.
Voters could then go on to vote for a candidate in the Reform Party
in the summer and cap off all of this multipartisan mischief with a
vote in November for one of the three people they helped nominate.
